						               													<description>Card Barrage is a head-to-head dexterity-based tower defense game. Players hone their dexterity skills and finesse at card tossing through attacking your opponent&amp;rsquo;s castle. At the start of the game, players lay out a card to represent their castle and its surrounding wall cards. Each turn, players physically toss cards against the other player&amp;rsquo;s castle and surrounding wall cards. Players score points when their barrage cards land on the other player&amp;rsquo;s castle or wall cards. Wall cards can be damaged and destroyed through attacks. You can play solo, head-to-head or team vs team. Rules govern how you can toss cards to attack through the lob, Frisbee, or flip method.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;OBJECTIVE &amp;ndash; The objective of Card barrage is to score points through attacking your opponents&amp;rsquo; castle and castle walls. Successfully tossed cards that land on your opponent&amp;rsquo;s castle or is surrounding wall cards will score a point.&amp;#10;GAME PLAY &amp;ndash; Each turn players may build a wall, upgrade a wall, and attack. Build a wall by playing a card into a previously destroyed wall section. Upgrade a wall by exchanging a wall card with a card in hand. If you did not build a wall, attack an opponent&amp;rsquo;s castle and wall by tossing a card to score points.&amp;#10;GAME END AND WINNING &amp;ndash; The game ends when one player has scored 10 points or destroyed all their opponent&amp;rsquo;s walls and then hits their opponent&amp;rsquo;s castle with all players getting an equal number of turns. The player with the most points wins.&amp;#10;THEME &amp;ndash; Medieval Setting and Castle sieges&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
